{
  "texts": [
    "In order to avoid voltage loses at the wires of the crossbar, we employed a Dual Side Connection scheme.",
    "Despite the increased peripheral circuitry complexity, this scheme improves the voltage delivery to each synapse 248 by connecting the two terminals of each wordline to the same input stimuli.",
    "The difference between Dual Side Connection and Single Side Connection is shown in Fig. 18.",
    "In practice, when designing the circuits for input voltage supply for the Dual Side Connection scheme on a chip, any mismatches and variations in voltages V i (Fig. 18b) should be avoided.",
    "The voltages V i from both sides of the crossbar should be identical with carefully designed communication wires."
  ]
}